My Dear girl-
a long delinquent letter to you My dear but I can feel so sure tha tyou do understand. 
I have been enjoying poor health for the last few days and tonight I am just as dull as I look. The weather is so beautiful and summery and such a teaser for anyone who likes to be out as I do, and I have been over doing in the yard the summer was so hot and dry, and my place was so late getting cleaned off. that I got very little plant Ed. So I have been planting roses and hedges of buck-
berry, Lillys goose berries raspberries and apples, cherries and peaches. (Just hedges of buck berry) Mona was real sick a week while John was aways and I went over there and played until she was able to-be up. 
John came home yester-day, having been gone seven weeks. He goes again the last of Jan. to <del/> East to the atlantic coast. He stopped at Butte Montana and visited with his sister Grace. So today and yesterday have been given over to "questions and answers"
We are having the loveliest Summer Weather here. warm 

