<unclear/> Thunder showers. Our cow-<unclear/> has good pasture. Oh by the way we will soon have a fresh cow and that means that I must <unclear/> while John is away again. I wish you could see my chickens and I am getting Eggs they find them selves and me too. And I just love to take care of them. I am sititng with the fireplace at my back oh how good the heat feels. And how often I wish for you to sit here with me. Sigurd wondered today if you were really sending money to come here. they all talk of you coming next summer. 
Mrs. Brown has bought a place just across the street from me. and won't it be nice when you come! She is a sport and loves the water, so you see me counting on a <unclear/> time when you come Miss Piper would you go to the photographer's ^in Lyons and see if he still has the <unclear/> from which he made my Enlarged picture that John has and if he has will you have him print me 1/2 doz. I must have one for a newspaper article of the Omaha Daily News. I gave John's bust to The Neihardt Society to present to the Omaha Public Library and there is to be an unveiling Sometime in the near future, and they want mine and Mona's and John's photos. Now dear if you could see to that for me and pay for than and send me the bill or tell them to send me the bill I"ll be very glad. Mona sends love. And of course you know I do Dear girl 
Alice M. Neihardt 